◆ DataOption

enum DataOption
Enumerator
DATA_PAD_00 

data padding with 0x00: XX XX XX XX 00 00 00 00

DATA_PAD_FF 

data padding with 0xff: XX XX XX XX ff ff ff ff

DATA_TRUNCATE_PAN 

truncate PAN (TLV tag 5A): 123456789FFFF => 123456789F

DATA_ADD_EMPTY 

add empty tags (with length 0) to result

DATA_TRUNCATE_DATA 

truncate, if data exceeds the fixed length

DATA_CONCATENATE 

concatenate tags without tag length information

DATA_EMV_TRACK2_EQUIVALENT 

format Track2 equivalent data (TLV tag 57) according EMV (w/o sentinel and LRC)

DATA_ASCII_CVV 

convert CVV (TLV tag DFA131) to ASCII format (string) w/o any padding

DATA_ASCII_PAN 

convert PAN (TLV tag 5A) to ASCII format (string) w/o any padding

DATA_ASCII_TRACK2_EQUIVALENT 

convert Track2 equivalent data (TLV tag 57) to ASCII format (string) w/o any padding

DATA_ASCII_EXPIRATION_DATE 

convert Expiration Date (TLV tag 5F24) to ASCII format (string) w/o any padding

DATA_ASCII_TRACK2 

convert pure Track2 data (TLV tag 57) to ASCII format (string) w/o any padding

◆ DialogOptions

enum DialogOptions

Dialog options

Enumerator
DLG_DISPLAY_ONLY 

display only (text without softkeys)

DLG_BEEP 

do a beep when displaying the dialog

DLG_CANCEL_KEY 

add cancel softkey to dialog. On press, RESULT_USER_CANCEL is returned. In addition, cancel key will result the same on devices with keyboard. For devices without touch an entry in helpers bar is displayed to signal user that the enter key can be pressed on the keyboard.

DLG_CLEAR_KEY 

add clear softkey to dialog. On press, RESULT_CLEAR_BUTTON is returned. In addition, clear key will result the same on devices with keyboard. For devices without touch an entry in helpers bar is displayed to signal user that the clear key can be pressed on the keyboard.

DLG_ENTER_KEY 

add enter softkey to dialog. On press, RESULT_OK is returned. In addition, enter key will result the same on devices with keyboard. For devices without touch an entry in helpers bar is displayed to signal user that t he enter key can be pressed on the keyboard.

DLG_NO_LEDS 

do not show LEDs even if enabled by enableLEDs()

DLG_CTLS_LOGO 

show CTLS logo on top of the dialog message (only when CTLS reader is in display)

DLG_QUESTION_LOGO 

show question logo on top of the dialog message (if no lower logo bit is set)

DLG_WARNING_LOGO 

show warning logo on top of the dialog message (if no lower logo bit is set)

DLG_ERROR_LOGO 

show error logo on top of the dialog message (if no lower logo bit is set)

DLG_SUCCESS_LOGO 

show success logo on top of the dialog message (if no lower logo bit is set)

DLG_WAIT_LOGO 

show wait logo/animation on top of the dialog message (if no lower logo bit is set)

DLG_ASYNC 

asynchronous dialog, which lets ui_dialog() return immediatelly

DLG_STORE_ASYNC_RESULT 

store asynchornous result to provide it with ui_getAsyncResult() after the dialog has been finished

DLG_HIDE_SOFT_KEYS 

hide softkeys on touch screen devices enabled by option DLG_CancelKey, DLG_ClearKey or DLG_EnterKey. For devices without touch, the entry in helpers bar will not apear. If the terminal has a keyboard, the dialog returns for the corresponding key stroke.

DLG_TEXT_ALIGN_LEFT 

text message shall be left aligned (default: horizontal centered)

DLG_TEXT_ALIGN_RIGHT 

text message shall be right aligned (default: horizontal centered, left-aligned is prior)

DLG_TEXT_ALIGN_TOP 

text message shall be top aligned (default: vertical centered)

DLG_TEXT_ALIGN_BOTTOM 

text message shall be bottom aligned (default: vertical centered, top-aligned is prior)

DLG_NO_HEADER 

don't display dialog header field (neither logo nor header text is displayed even if provided with variable "header_text"

DLG_CLEAR_ON_RETURN 

clear content before the dialog returns

DLG_ABORT_ON_CARD_REMOVE 

abort the dialog, if the card is removed (returns RESULT_FAIL)

DLG_IGNORE_EXT_ABORT 

ignore external abort by check4Interrupt, otherwise the dialog can be aborted by mobile device (e.g. lost link). External abort will return RESULT_MOBILE_ABORT or RESULT_NO_LINK (ignored, if DLG_Async is not set)

◆ EMVAppFlowCapabilityBits

enum EMVAppFlowCapabilityBits

EMV flow capability bit numbers

Enumerator
EMV_CT_FORCE_RISK_MANAGEMENT 

Perform risk management in every case.

EMV_CT_BLACKLIST 

Support of blacklist (exception list), the callback set by SDIClient::setEMVCallback (EMV_CB_CHECK_LOG_HOTLIST) will be invoked
Depends on EMV_CT_TXNOP_HOTLST_LOG_CALLBACK and EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS

EMV_CT_TRANSACTION_LOG 

Support transaction log, the callback set by SDIClient::setEMVCallback (EMV_CB_CHECK_LOG_HOTLIST) will be invoked
Depends on EMV_CT_TXNOP_HOTLST_LOG_CALLBACK and EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS

EMV_CT_PIN_BYPASS 

PIN bypass supported

EMV_CT_FORCE_ONLINE 

Feature "Force online" supported

EMV_CT_FORCE_ACCEPTANCE 

Feature "Force acceptance" supported

EMV_CT_CASH_SUPPORT 

Support of cash transactions

EMV_CT_CASHBACK_SUPPORT 

Support of cashback transactions

EMV_CT_CHECK_INCONS_TRACK2_PAN 

Check consistency of track2 equivalent data (EMV_TRACK2_EQUIVALENT_DATA) provided by ICC.
Mandated for MasterCard and Amex.
Validate format and that contents matches to EMV_PAN and EMV_EXPIRATION_DATE.
See also EMV_CT_FALLBACK_ON_INCONS_TRACK2.

EMV_CT_CONF_AMOUNT_PIN 

Confirm amount and enter PIN in one display.
Invoking callback for amount confirmation depends on EMV_CT_TXNOP_AMOUNT_CONF.
May be deactivated by EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS.

EMV_CT_DOMESTIC_CHECK 

the callback set by SDIClient::setEMVCallback (EMV_CB_LOCAL_CHECKS) will be called.
Needs to be activated per transaction by EMV_CT_TXNOP_LOCAL_CHCK_CALLBACK.
May be deactivated by EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS.

EMV_CT_TRANSACTION_TYPE_17_FOR_CASH 

Enable mapping of transaction type for cash transaction from 0x01 to 0x17

EMV_CT_CHECK_INCONS_TRACK2_NO_EXP 

Check consistency of track2 equivalent data (EMV_TRACK2_EQUIVALENT_DATA) provided by ICC.
Mandated for MasterCard and Amex.
Validate format and that contents matches to EMV_PAN
Only effective if EMV_CT_CHECK_INCONS_TRACK2_PAN is deactivated. See also EMV_CT_FALLBACK_ON_INCONS_TRACK2.

EMV_CT_TRANSACTION_TYPE_30_FOR_PREAUTH 

Amex Pre-Authorization with transaction type 30 Use EMV_ADK_TRAN_TYPE_AMEX_PREAUTH for pre-authorization resp. reservation transactions. The modified transaction type is used towards card and put out in tag 9C.

EMV_CT_REFERRAL_AFTER_TXN 

In case voice referral is required: Chip transaction is terminated with AAC. Referral transaction is performed subsequently as "CardNotPresent" (German handling).

EMV_CT_DCC_CHECK 

Enable DCC (Dynamic currency conversion).
Invocation depends on EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS, EMV_CT_TXNOP_DCC_CALLBACK, and EMV_CT_TXNOP_DCC_CALLBACK_ALWAYS.

EMV_CT_REFUND_CONFIRM_AMOUNT 

Confirm amount during refund transaction
Invoking callback for amount confirmation depends on EMV_CT_TXNOP_AMOUNT_CONF and EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS.

EMV_CT_USE_CFG_APPL_NAME 

Use configured application name instead of EMVCo rule (9F12 prior to 50 prior to configured). Effective for cardholder's application selection.

EMV_CT_FALLBACK_ON_INCONS_TRACK2 

Valid only in case of activated EMV_CT_CHECK_INCONS_TRACK2_PAN.
If activated: Check will be done before Cardholder Verification. In case of fail EMV ADK will process fallback handling (may result in EMV_STATUS_FALLBACK). E.g. required for German dcpos 2.4, may be used for "M/Chip Functional Architecture", AMEX ED-031 in test plan ver. 4.2.
If not activated: Check will be done just before processing 1st cryptogram. If fail: GENAC1 will be requested with AAC. E.g. required for MasterCard REQ22, AMEX ED-031 in Swedish AMEX test plan 1.0.

EMV_CT_AMOUNT_CONFIRM_ON_SIGNATURE 

Customer amount confirmation in case of CVM signature
Invoking callback for amount confirmation depends on EMV_CT_TXNOP_AMOUNT_CONF and EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS.

EMV_CT_SDA_SELECTED_TVR_ON 

Activate the support of the TVR byte SDA selected, introduced in Nov 2013 for kernels not yet supporting this feature, configurable per AID (for kernels supporting this it'll eb always activated, config is don't care)

EMV_CT_CASHBACK_OFFLINE_SUPPORT 

If set cash back transactions are not automatically forced online.

EMV_CT_REFUND_PROCESSING_RESTRICTIONS 

Perform Processing restrictions for Refund transactions (French Refund Requirements).

EMV_CT_REFUND_NO_GENERATE_AC 

Do not perform Generate AC when finishing Refund transactions (French Refund Requirements).

EMV_CT_REFUND_FLOW_INTERAC 

Perform full EMV transaction although transaction type is refund.

EMV_CT_REFUND_NO_ZERO_AMOUNT 

Do NOT set the amount to zero in CDOL1 for Refund transactions with Generate AC.

EMV_CT_DPAS_DATA_STORAGE_SUPPORT 

Support of Data Storage for D-PAS Connect. Useful only for Discover AIDs.

EMV_CT_DPAS_EXTENDED_LOGGING_SUPPORT 

Support of Extended Logging for D-PAS Connect. Useful only for Discover AIDs.

EMV_CT_DPAS_CDCVM_SUPPORT 

Support of Consumer Device CVM for D-PAS Connect. Useful only for Discover AIDs.

EMV_CT_APP_FLOW_VISA_QUASI_CASH 

Convert transaction type from '01' to '11' indicating VISA Quasi Cash. Use in conjunction with EMV_CT_APPLIDATA_TYPE. TxnTypesCash if AUC checks shall be applied, that is both values '01' and '11' should be set.

EMV_CT_APP_FLOW_CASHBACK_TRANS_TYPE_00 

Convert transaction type from '09' to '00' indicating Cashback. This is a VISA L3 requirement for new L3 test cases. Use in conjunction with EMV_CT_APPLIDATA_TYPE. TxnTypesCashback if AUC checks shall be applied, that is both values '00' and '09' should be set.

EMV_CTLS_DOM_NO_FINAL_SELECT 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Do not perform the final select if the AID belongs to a nonEMV/Domestic kernel

EMV_CTLS_LOA_ENABLE 

(Vel: y VFI: y) Enable list of applications processing for this AID (per default not recommended for CTLS txns because directory file is available)

EMV_CTLS_CASH_SUPPORT 

(Vel: y VFI: y) Support of cash transactions

EMV_CTLS_CASHBACK_SUPPORT 

(Vel: y VFI: y) Support of cashback transactions

EMV_CTLS_OMIT_NOT_ALLOWED_SELECTION 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Omit not allowed candidates already during Entry Point selection process, e.g. above CTLS transaction limit. However: Warning: The EP defines Contactless transaction Limit >=, while MasterCard PP3 defines it as >. So do not set it for MasterCard AIDs

EMV_CTLS_FORCE_ENTRY_POINT 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Force Entry Point processing of the former EMVCo Entry Point specification

EMV_CTLS_FORCE_KERNEL_USAGE 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Force Kernel ID to be used, even if EP tag 9F2A is available

EMV_CTLS_LIST_OF_AIDS_IF_PPSE_MISSING_ONLY 

(Vel: y VFI: y) List of AIDs method only if PPSE directory does not exist in a card with the corresponding AID. Precondition: EMV_CTLS_LOA_ENABLE is set.

EMV_CTLS_LIST_OF_AIDS_IF_PPSE_FAILED_ONLY 

(Vel: n VFI: y) List of AIDs method only if PPSE directory exists in the card but a response for PPSE request was badly formatted and PPSE stage failed. Precondition: EMV_CTLS_LOA_ENABLE is set.

EMV_CTLS_CARD_READ_TXN_ZERO_AMOUNT 

(Vel: y VFI: y) If this bit is set then the reader will send an amount of zero to the card for card read transactions, otherwise the reader will send the normal amount

EMV_CTLS_SKIP_CARDSELECTION_APPS 

(Vel: y VFI: n) If this bit is set this AID will be skipped if requiring explicit cardholder selection

EMV_CTLS_SKIP_TXN_LIMIT_CHECK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) If this bit is set for this AID the transaction limit check will be skipped and the AID remains in the candidate list

EMV_CTLS_FORCE_ONLINE 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Feature "Force online" supported

EMV_CTLS_WAIT_CARD_REMOVAL_END 

(Vel: y VFI: y) Wait for card removal at the end of an EMV transaction before returning to application (on TC, AAC and ARQC --> Card Read Complete)

EMV_CTLS_START_REMOVAL_DETECTION 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Start card removal procedure after kernel processing. This enables the service SDIClient::emvCtlsCardRemoval.
Only effective on deactivated EMV_CTLS_WAIT_CARD_REMOVAL_END

EMV_CTLS_EP_EXTENDED_SELECTION 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Enable the Entry Point extended selection (9F29 is used if present on ICC)

EMV_CTLS_MULTIPLE_AID_KERNEL_ID 

(Vel: y VFI: n) byte 2 of kernel id is used to store multiple configurations of same kernel Id-AID pair. If this flag is set the 3rd byte of the kernel id is set to zero in the Terminal Candidate List which is presented to the EntryPoint while the original value is used towards application interface.

EMV_CTLS_ENABLE_OFFLINE_CASHBACK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Do not apply business rule: "Cash back is online only". Instead rely on terminal and card risk management. Anyhow the application might force the transaction online by transaction flow option.
Caution: For Visa like schemes (Visa, Visa-AP, Discover and UPI) this flag has a different effect: It suppresses the mandory reduction of the floor limit to zero.

EMV_CTLS_RESET_TXN_TYPE 

(Vel: y VFI: n) A custom transaction type ('9C') might be used during kernel processing in a virtual terminal for card read transactions. Therefore tag '9C' has to be configured using EMVConf::setAdditionalTags() If this flag is raised the transaction type in the kernel database will be reset after completion (e.g. to '20' for refund) in order to hide this modification from the outside world (vouchers, host messages)

EMV_CTLS_CFG_APPL_NAME 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Always use default application label EMV_CTLS_APPLIDATA_SCHEME_SPECIFIC_STRUCT::DefaultApplicationName_DFAB22 in result data EMV_CTLS_TRANSRES_STRUCT::AppName

EMV_CTLS_CARD_READ_SKIP_TXN_LIMIT_CHECK 

B3b5: (Vel: y VFI: n) If this bit is set for this AID the transaction limit check will be skipped for card read transactions and the AID remains in the candidate list

◆ EMVCtlsReaderOptions

enum EMVCtlsReaderOptions

SDI CTLS card reader options (bit mask)

Enumerator
EMV_CTLS_RFU_1 

reserved for probable reader number

EMV_CTLS_RESET_KEEP_FIELD_ON 

(Vel: y VFI: n) EMV_CTLS_SmartReset() ucOptions: Do not switch off RF field when no card was detected. CAUTION: This results in higher power consumption and might cause overheating problems.

EMV_CTLS_RFU_3 

had been EMV_CTLS_SPURIOUS_DETECT before which was deprecated since August 2020

EMV_CTLS_SPURIOUS_DETECT 
Deprecated:
switch off the workaround for spurious card detections on ADK level (workaround for L1 issues, code provided by platform team), siwthcing off may provide better detection of 2 cards in field, which is resolved with the spurious card detection workaround.
EMV_CTLS_EMV_COMPLIANT 

(Vel: y VFI: n) EMV_CTLS_SmartReset() ucOptions: force EMV compliancy during card detection (e.g. MiFare detection deactivated), no detection of hybrid cards (e.g. EMV+MiFare), no UID detection. This feature is mutually exclusive with EMV_CTLS_RESET_NO_EMV.

EMV_CTLS_RESET_NO_EMV 

(Vel: y VFI: n) EMV_CTLS_SmartReset() ucOptions: Card detection without EMV compliancy (EMV cards are also detected, but timing is different). This feature is mutually exclusive with EMV_CTLS_EMV_COMPLIANT.

EMV_CTLS_RESET_PICC_OPEN_ONLY 
Deprecated:
(Vel: y VFI: n) EMV_CTLS_SmartReset() ucOptions: Only initialise CTLS reader, do not detect cards.
EMV_CTLS_SKIP_FIELD_ON 

(Vel: n VFI: y) EMV_CTLS_SmartReset() ucOptions: Tell VFI Reader to consider RF Field is already turned on by NFC ADK.

EMV_CTLS_OPEN_READER 

(Vel: y VFI: n) option for EMV_CTLS_SmartPowerOff, initialise CTLS reader. Use in combination EMV_CTLS_OPEN_READER for re-open.

EMV_CTLS_CLOSE_READER 

(Vel: y VFI: n) option for EMV_CTLS_SmartPowerOff, close CTLS reader. Use in combination EMV_CTLS_OPEN_READER for re-open.

EMV_CTLS_DETECT_REMOVAL 

(Vel: y VFI: n) option for EMV_CTLS_SmartPowerOff, start removal detection background task

◆ EMVCtReaderOptions

enum EMVCtReaderOptions

SDI CT card reader options (bit mask)

Enumerator
EMV_CT_CUSTOMER 

bit 1,2 used for reader selection: Customer Card Slot

EMV_CT_SAM_1 

bit 1,2 used for reader selection: SAM1

EMV_CT_SAM_2 

bit 1,2 used for reader selection: SAM2

EMV_CT_SAM_3 

bit 1,2 used for reader selection: SAM3

EMV_CT_TRY_PPS 

Try to increase the baudrate by using PPS.

EMV_CT_SKIP_ATR 

Skip ATR reading, not included in response.

EMV_CT_TRY_PPS_EPA 

PPS handling for Austrian Maestro Cards.

EMV_CT_WARMRESET 

Warm Reset to ICC (Cold reset must have been applied before)

EMV_CT_SAM_EMV_MODE 

SAMs are reset in mode ISO 7816 per default, use this bit to switch to EMV 311 (for SAMs only)

EMV_CT_DETECT_WRONG_ATR 

Distinguish between wrong ATR and card wrong side/no chip and return applicable return value (for customer slot only)

EMV_CT_CARD_CLASS_B_3V 

For class B (3V) cards

EMV_CT_ID0_ISO_MODE 

The customer card (ID 0) is reset in mode EMV per default, use this bit to switch to ISO 7816 (for ID0 only)

◆ EMVDomesticOptionBits

enum EMVDomesticOptionBits

domestic option bits

Enumerator
EMV_DOM_AUSTRIAN_NGV 

Continue transaction as Austrian Non Guaranteed Payment.

EMV_DOM_TXN_INTERCEPT 

Intercept transaction. Context will remain. Repetition transaction must be started with EMV_TXN_REPEAT_TXN_INTERCEPT.

EMV_DOM_ABORT_NO_TEXT 

if the EMV callback set by SDIClient::setEMVCallback() with (EMV_CB_DOMESTIC_APPS) returns FALSE and uc_manipulation != EMV_STATUS_AAC: Don't display texts EMV_TXT_PROCESSING_ERROR and EMV_TXT_REMOVE_CARD
Otherwise not effective

EMV_DOM_TIP_OFF 

convert a tip capable transaction back to sale transaction (used for countries where tip with signature is done outside the scope of EMV and returns the txn to a normal sale transaction)

◆ EMVFetchOptions

enum EMVFetchOptions

options for emvCtFetchTxnTags

Enumerator
EMV_FETCH_NO_EMPTY 

In case no data is found for a given TLV tag: don't include this tag in the output.

EMV_FETCH_KERNEL 

Search tags only in kernel database, excluding kernel private tags ("readHypTag"). Data originated from kernel, ICC and EMV_CT_APPLIDATA_STRUCT::Additional_Tags_TRM can be found. To be used in case of double definition of tags.

EMV_FETCH_ADK 

Search tags only in the ADK configuration database. Data originated from EMV_CT_APPLIDATA_TYPE and EMV_CT_TERMDATA_STRUCT can be found. To be used in case of double definition of tags.

EMV_FETCH_KERNEL_PRV 

Search tags only in kernel private database ("readHypTag").

◆ EMVFlowOptionBits

enum EMVFlowOptionBits

EMV terminal flow option bits

Enumerator
EMV_CTLS_VISA_WAVE 

Support for Visa wave
for VFI reader or enabling Raptor VISA AP kernel (PDOL decision)
Info: VFI reader tag DF64, 1FF0 and others - This feature is not configurable per AID only global

EMV_CTLS_OR_NONEMV_MARKET 

Support for Amex EMV or NON EMV market
Map to Byte2 BIT1 of Contactless Kernel Options(1FF0)
Info: VFI reader tag 1FF0 - This feature is not configurable per AID only global

EMV_CTLS_UI_SCHEME_DEFAULT 

VFI reader only: Use reader's UI scheme "default", as standard "EMEA" is used.
Visa Europe tests will fail if this is activated. But it's needed for display callback "L1 error" (EMV_TXT_RETAP_SAME_L1)

EMV_CTLS_AL_USE_TID 

Use the TID as IFD Serial number. Background: If application can not provide IFD_Serial this can be used as replacement to have a unique value available (not for VFI-Reader).

EMV_CTLS_LED_NON_VISA_EUROPE 

Switch off Visa Europe work around for LED2. This option is like EMV_CTLS_UI_SCHEME_DEFAULT but for VERTEX.

EMV_CTLS_LED_EP_OPTION_2 

Use LED scheme option 2 as defined in Entry Point spec [EMV BB]. Coloured LEDs similar to Visa Wave 2 (Visa Asia Pacific). For LED configuration see EMV_CTLS_LED_ConfigDesign_Extended().

EMV_CTLS_LED_INTERAC 

Use LED blinking scheme for Interac (Canada)

EMV_CTLS_FORWARD_VFI_FAIL 

VFI Reader final scenario "Fail" is forwarded to the application by returning EMV_ADK_VFI_FAIL instead of per default EMV_ADK_AAC. Additionnally the ADK provides the SW12 in T_DF64_KernelDebugData[0]&[1], VFI Reader Error Code in T_DF64_KernelDebugData[3], and VFI Reader RF State Code in T_DF64_KernelDebugData[30]

EMV_CTLS_DISABLE_DISCOVER_ZIP_CHECK 

VFI Reader only: Disable the check according to D-PAS 1.0 Bulletin TAS-002 v1.0 which requires to consider the legacy Discover ZIP application as mandatory on any card/phone with the Discover/Diners D-PAS AID, and to reject the card if ZIP is not present

EMV_CTLS_ALERT_TONE_ON_DECLINE_VK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Per default the tone indicates if card read successful or not. Outcome of the transaction is not indicated. With this option an additional alert tone is sounded in case transaction is declined.

EMV_CTLS_GET_DATA_9F68_VK

EMV_CTLS_ENABLE_TAGS_AT_GPO_VK

EMV_CTLS_ZERO_CHECK_DISABLE_VK

EMV_CTLS_ODO_SUPPORT_VK

EMV_CTLS_ODO_SDA_VK

EMV_CTLS_ODO_DDA_VK

EMV_CTLS_ODO_SDA_ERR_ONLINE_VK

EMV_CTLS_CASHBACK_TRANS_TYPE_VK9_VK

EMV_CTLS_DO_NOT_CFG_9F21_TIME_VK

EMV_CTLS_CARDREAD_GENAC1_ARQC_AK 

B1b1: (Vel: y VFI: n) Card read transaction (e.g. refund): request ARQC in GENAC1, usually AAC is requested

EMV_CTLS_TRANSACTION_TYPE_30_FOR_PREAUTH_AK 

B1b2: (Vel: y VFI: n) Amex Pre-Authorization with transaction type 30
Use EMV_ADK_TRAN_TYPE_AMEX_PREAUTH for pre-authorization resp. reservation transactions
The modified transaction type is used towards card and put out in EMV_CTLS_TRANSRES_STRUCT::T_9C_TransType.

Note
Pre-Authorization and reservation transactions are equivalent. They are initiated with EMV_ADK_TRAN_TYPE_INIT_RESERVATION_A or EMV_ADK_TRAN_TYPE_INIT_RESERVATION_B.
EMV_CTLS_STATUS_CHECK_ENABLE_AK 

B1b3: (Vel: y VFI: y) Enable status check for one single unit of currency (1$ txn is going online for status check)

EMV_CTLS_ZERO_CHECK_ENABLE_ONLINE_AK

EMV_CTLS_DISABLE_9F6E_KERNEL_VERSION_AK

EMV_CTLS_MULTIPLE_RANDOM_NUMBERS_JK

EMV_CTLS_CASHBACK_NOT_FORCED_CVM_DK

EMV_CTLS_DATA_STORAGE_DK

EMV_CTLS_REQUEST_CDA_WITH_ARQC_IK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) On first GAC do request CDA despite cryptogram type is ARQC (P1 = '90').

EMV_CTLS_REFUND_FLOW_INTERAC_IK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Do not force AppAction to decline and do not modify and TAC or limit. Note: Unless otherwise specified by regional needs, Interac flow should be enabled for Interac AIDs.

EMV_CTLS_READ_CARD_REFUND_EK

EMV_CTLS_CHECK_INCONS_TRACK2_PAN_PK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Check consistency of track2 equivalent data (EMV_TRACK2_EQUIVALENT_DATA) provided by ICC. Validate format and that contents matches to EMV_PAN. Visa Europe stuff VppT

EMV_CTLS_CASHBACK_NOT_FORCED_CVM_PK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Per default cashback transactions require CVM and are forced online by setting floorlimit to 0, you can use standard CVM limit and floorlimit if you set this flag

EMV_CTLS_STATUS_CHECK_ENABLE_CK 

(Vel: y VFI: y) Enable status check for one single unit of currency (1$ txn is going online for status check)

EMV_CTLS_ZERO_CHECK_ENABLE_SKIP_CK 

(Vel: y VFI: y) Enable zero check for zero amount transaction, skip AID for zero amount

EMV_CTLS_ZERO_CHECK_ENABLE_ONLINE_CK 

(Vel: y VFI: y) Enable zero check for zero amount transaction, going online for zero amount txns

EMV_CTLS_CHECK_INCONS_TRACK2_PAN_CK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Check consistency of track2 equivalent data (EMV_TRACK2_EQUIVALENT_DATA) provided by ICC. Validate format and that contents matches to EMV_PAN. Visa Europe stuff VppT

EMV_CTLS_CASHBACK_NOT_FORCED_CVM_CK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Per default cashback transactions require CVM and are forced online by setting floorlimit to 0, you can use standard CVM limit and floorlimit if you set this flag

EMV_CTLS_ENABLE_FDDA_VERSION_CK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Per default the legacy fDDA version 0 is switched off. If you want to support it on top of the up date fDDA version 1. you can enable it by setting this bit

EMV_CTLS_DISABLE_PIN_BELOW_CVM_CK 

(Vel: y VFI: y) Do not ask for online PIN and Signature for transactions below CVM Limit when this was requested by card. This bit should be set for Credit / Quasi Credit AIDs according to Ref. "UPI QuickPass Implementation Guide for Acquirers v1.3.9": Terminals shall not ask for online PIN when all of below situations are met -QuickPass credit/Quasi credit cards are accepted, -Contactless transaction amount is below CVM limit of the terminal.

EMV_CTLS_SUPPORT_APPLI_AUTHENTICATE_GK 

(Vel: y VFI: y) Support for special transaction type "Application Authentication Transaction", see also EMV_TXN_AUTHENTICATE

EMV_CTLS_SUPPORT_GETDATA_GK 

(Vel: y VFI: y) Support for special transaction type "Retrieve application data elements using GET DATA command", see also EMV_TXN_GETDATA

EMV_CTLS_SUPPORT_PUTDATA_GK 

(Vel: y VFI: y) Support for special transaction type "Update application data elements using PUT DATA command", see also EMV_TXN_PUTDATA

EMV_CTLS_AMOUNT_MULTIPLY_100_GK 

B1b4: (Vel: y VFI: n) Vietnam VCCS special feature: Multiply amount by 100 before using it in GENAC1

EMV_CTLS_SERVICE_FEATURE_ENABLE_RK 

(Vel: y VFI: y) Rupay Service Feature Enable/Disable

EMV_CTLS_TORN_TRANSACTION_INDICATOR_RK 

(Vel: y VFI: y) Rupay Torn Transaction Indicator

EMV_CTLS_READ_RECORD_SFI1_QDDA_RK 

(Vel: n VFI: y) Perform READ RECORD of SFI 1 only when qDDA is disabled

EMV_CTLS_MULTIPLE_RANDOM_NUMBERS_RK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Generate new random number ('9F37') with each kernel activation, that is 2nd GAC

EMV_CTLS_ONLINE_PIN_SUPPORTED_RK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Online PIN supported

EMV_CTLS_SIGNATURE_SUPPORTED_RK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Signature supported

EMV_CTLS_ON_DEVICE_CVM_SUPPORTED_RK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) On-Device CVM (mobile CVM) supported

EMV_CTLS_CVM_REQUIRED_RK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) CVM required, transaction will fail in case card decision is "no CVM)

EMV_CTLS_ISSUER_UPDATE_SUPPORTED_RK 

(Vel: y VFI: n) Issuer script processing supported

EMV_CTLS_STATUS_CHECK_ENABLE_WK 

B1b1: Enable status check for one single unit of currency (one major currency unit, e.g. 1€ is going online for status check). If TTQ 'online capable reader' is not set, 'Contactless Application Not Allowed' indicator will be set

EMV_CTLS_ZERO_CHECK_ENABLE_SKIP_WK

EMV_CTLS_ZERO_CHECK_ENABLE_ONLINE_WK

EMV_CTLS_NO_CDCVM_WK

EMV_CTLS_EXPLICIT_SELECT_DOM

◆ EMVOptions

enum EMVOptions

EMV initialization options

Enumerator
EMV_OPT_BASE_INIT 

base init: set options and register callback, but do not allocate memory

EMV_OPT_L1_DUMP 
Deprecated:
not supported anymore as non-kernel tags are collected by default
EMV_OPT_AUTO_RETAP 

Do NOT handle retaps as two separate transactions but handle retaps internally and fire message events only to the app (TAG_BF14_CBK_TEXT_DISPLAY), the retap returncodes (like EMV_ADK_TXN_CTLS_MOBILE) will not appear in this case but processing is handled on ADK level. – Detailed explanation: – VFI-Reader: The VFI-reader in general manges the retap for a mobile internally, ALWAYS. There is no chance for the ADK hand over the retap for a moblie transaction to the application. Therefore the EMV_ADK_TXN_CTLS_MOBILE does NEVER appear with VRFI-Reader. – Velocity: On velovcity the kernel is NEVER handling the retap internally. So the ADK can hand it over to the application. Then you would receive EMV_ADK_TXN_CTLS_MOBILE. For compatibility reasons with the VFI-Reader we have introduced that the ADK is handling the mobile retap optionally. This is configurable with this parameter. If you configure this, then also the EMV_ADK_TXN_CTLS_MOBILE is NEVER returned to the application. If you do not configure it this returncode will appear. – Only if internal handling of the Velocity or the VFI-Reader takes place, the BF14 callback is issued to allow the application to display something. If the configuration is in that way that the app wants to handle the mobile retap according to its needs, then the BF14 is NEVER invoked. This is mutually exclusive.

EMV_OPT_CONFIG_MODE 

configuration is only written to files upon ExitFramework and ApplyConfiguration instead of written upon each configuration function -> performance improvement

EMV_OPT_USE_DEF_VT_CAPK 

Use "EMV_CTLS_Keys.xml" for the CAPKeys of ALL virtual terminals. This option is to be set by the initialization of the virtual terminal 0 only. Once set this feature applies to all virtual terminals.

EMV_OPT_DELETE_ALL 

delete all existing configuration files using the same virtual terminal

EMV_OPT_USE_VFI 

Decrecated

EMV_OPT_USE_VERTEX 

Decrecated

EMV_OPT_TRACE 

switch on EMV trace

EMV_OPT_TRACE_CLT 

switch on client trace

EMV_OPT_LED_CBK_EXT 

request external LED display. Per default the LEDs are displayed in the configured region by using the GUI ADK. It is highly recommended to use this default for speed reasons. It is possible to offer a callback so that LEDs can be managed on apps side by using this callback (TAG_BF10_CTLS_CBK_LEDS).

EMV_OPT_TRACE_SYSLOG 

use syslog instead of callback for trace. Not possible for Verix.

EMV_OPT_LED_VFI_INT 

VFI Reader only: request internal LED display. If set, LED handling is done internally by the VFI Reader. If not set, LED display depends on EMV_CTLS_INIT_OPT_LED_CBK_EXT.

EMV_OPT_VFI_BUZZER_ADK 

VFI Reader only: Buzzer is not done by VFI reader, ADK takes over the beeps. see also EMV_CTLS_TERMDATA_STRUCT::BeepVolume.

EMV_OPT_CALC_CHKSUM 

Calculate checksums of configuration files, may lead to setting of result bit EMV_CTLS_INIT_RES_CHKSUM_DIFF.

EMV_OPT_NEW_CFG_INTF 
Deprecated:
new application configuration interface is the only processing and this flag is ignored
EMV_OPT_BEEP_CBK_EXT 

Activate beeper callback (TAG_BF19_CTLS_CBK_BEEP). Per default beeper is controlled by EMV ADK.

EMV_OPT_TRACE_ADK_LOG 

use ADK-LOG instead of callback for trace

EMV_OPT_TIMINGS 

measure card and terminal performance. Note: For this feature other trace output is switched off

EMV_OPT_SHARED_CONFIG 

On VOS/VOS2 use /mnt/flash/etc/config/adkemv for persistence instead of $HOME/flash. NOTE: Only tje processes very first EMV_CTLS_Init_Framework decides the shared config mode.

EMV_OPT_EPP_MASTER 

Generate a Configuration Id for every configuration change at time of persisting. Generate a checksum for every persistence file to be aware of changes via file system. The configuration id is specific to a Virtual Terminal and returned on Init Framework and when the configuration is stored to the file system. It is seen on serial interface only.

EMV_OPT_VIRT_1 

virtual terminal 1: configuration and transaction not done with the standard terminal but virtual terminal No X

EMV_OPT_VIRT_2 

virtual terminal 2: configuration and transaction not done with the standard terminal but virtual terminal No X

EMV_OPT_VIRT_3 

virtual terminal 3: configuration and transaction not done with the standard terminal but virtual terminal No X

EMV_OPT_VIRT_4 

virtual terminal 4: configuration and transaction not done with the standard terminal but virtual terminal No X

EMV_STATUS_TIMEOUT 

Timeout

EMV_STATUS_MAX_CFG_NUMBER_EXCEEDED 

CTLS: Number of keys uploaded to VFI Reader exceeded (appears when number of keys more than 99, all next keys are ignored)

EMV_STATUS_VFI_FAIL 

VFI Reader "Fail" result. Transaction is terminated and application should decide about the final outcome (decline, fallback, try another card, etc...) based on the VFI Reader response data items (Error Code - SW1 - SW2 - RF State Code). This is returned only with VFI Reader and only if the Terminal Flow Option INPUT_CTLS_TRM_FLOWOPT_FORWARD_VFI_FAIL is set, otherwise EMV_STATUS_AAC is returned per default.

EMV_STATUS_CTLS_OFFLINE_PIN 

Transaction to be continued after PIN input for girocard (German debit card) Offline PIN CVM

EMV_STATUS_NOT_ACCEPTED 

Transaction / Payment type not accepted

EMV_STATUS_CANCELLED 

Transaction was cancelled by EMV_CTLS_Break()

EMV_STATUS_CARD_LOG_LOG_OK 

Return code for successful read of cards transaction log (currently qPBOC only)

EMV_STATUS_CTLS_LOW_BATTERY 

Return code for EMV_CTLS_SetupTransaction indicating mobile device's battery too low for contactless transaction.

EMV_STATUS_NOT_ALLOWED_WRONG_CFG_INTF 

CTLS: The function is not allowed when using this config interface

EMV_STATUS_VIRTTERMMAP_WRONG_INIT 
EMV_STATUS_TOO_MANY_TAPS 
EMV_STATUS_CAN_NOT_PROCESS 
EMV_STATUS_USE_ANOTHER_CTLS_CARD 

CTLS: advice the customer to use another CTLS card (will appear only if the CTLS kernel is configured in that way that Contact Chip is not supported)

EMV_STATUS_USE_OTHER_TERMINAL 

CTLS: advice the merchant to use another terminal to process the transaction (Interac spec requirement)

EMV_STATUS_SCRIPT_PROCESSING_COMPLETE 

CTLS: explicit script processing completed (CTLS, e.g. Discover DPAS)

EMV_STATUS_FALLBACK_CHIP_ONLY 

CTLS: Fallback to chip (CTLS), no msr allowed

EMV_STATUS_READER_CMD_NOT_ALLOWED 

VFI-Reader: Returned by EMV_CTLS_SetupTransaction() and EMV_CTLS_ContinueOffline() if VFI-Reader responds to "Activate Transaction" with "Command not allowed". This happens if VFI-Reader has not yet finished last transaction, e.g. is still waiting for ContinueOnline.

EMV_STATUS_NOT_ALLOWED 

Parallel function call not allowed

EMV_STATUS_CTLS_NOT_AVAILABLE 

CTLS not present on hardware per OS information

EMV_STATUS_USR_BCKSPC_KEY_PRESSED 

Application requested return for E_USR_BACKSPACE_KEY_PRESSED, not used anymore

EMV_STATUS_CEILING_LIMIT 

CTLS: amount is above the ceiling limit for CTLS (either terminal ceiling limit or highest scheme ceiling limit)

EMV_STATUS_CTLS_RETAP_SAME 

CTLS: start over with re-tapping the same card (deactivation/activation/start txn)

EMV_STATUS_CTLS_DOMESTIC_APP 

CTLS: Domestic Application Kernel selected

EMV_STATUS_NO_CARD 

CTLS: No card processing so far

EMV_STATUS_NOAPP 

CT: Return code if application not found by EMV_CT_CheckSupportedAID().
CTLS: Empty terminal candidate list (e.g. all application's ceiling limits exceeded) at EMV_CTLS_SetupTransaction().

EMV_STATUS_NO_EXEC 

CT & CTLS: not executable

EMV_STATUS_ARQC 

CT & CTLS: Transaction must be performed online

EMV_STATUS_TC 

CT & CTLS: Transaction performed (offline / online)

EMV_STATUS_AAC 

CT & CTLS: Transaction declined

EMV_STATUS_AAR 

CT: Transaction cancellation (former "card referral"), not used anymore

EMV_STATUS_PARAM 

CT & CTLS: Parameter error (wrong parameter was passed to the function)

EMV_STATUS_CARDERR 

CT & CTLS: Proprietary card error (actually converted to EMV_STATUS_FALLBACK)

EMV_STATUS_BADAPP 

CT: Repeat EMV_Select function call-up because selected application on the proprietary card is erroneous. The currently selected application must be transferred (not NO_APPLI) -> this leads to new application selection but the candidate list is not reconstructed.

EMV_STATUS_CVM 

CT: User abort during PIN input (cancel button, timeout, card removed)

EMV_STATUS_ABORT 

On transaction function it means that current transaction must be aborted.
On configuration function it represents "failed".

EMV_STATUS_CARD_BLOCKED 

CT & CTLS: Blocked card, regional dependent if fallback to magstripe should be done

EMV_STATUS_CARDERR_FORMAT 

Card error e.g. erroneous TLV coding, incorrect data -> no transaction cancellation

EMV_STATUS_INTERNAL 

CT & CTLS: e.g. erroneous communication to PINPad, internal error, not (completely) initialized (function not allowed due to EMV_CT_Init_Framework() with EMV_CT_INIT_OPT_BASE_INIT()
EMV_CTLS_Init_Framework() with EMV_CTLS_INIT_OPT_BASE_INIT() )

EMV_STATUS_ONLINE_PIN_RETRY 

CT: Online PIN reentered (PIN check).
EMV_CT_ContinueOnline()/EMV_CTLS_ContinueOnline() will return this value in the following scenario: Online PIN was entered. Host returned "PIN wrong".
Calling application must contact host again. And afterwards call EMV_CT_ContinueOnline() / EMV_CTLS_ContinueOnline() once again.

EMV_STATUS_SAVE_ERROR 

Writing config files failed. ANSI C functions fopen(), fwrite(), or fclose() gave back error. Make sure that file access rights are setup correctly.

EMV_STATUS_APP_BLOCKED 

Application blocked: AID evaluation at fallback, no global fallback because it is not allowed for this special blocked application

EMV_STATUS_READ_ERROR 

Error while reading EMV configuration

EMV_STATUS_ERR_HSM 

E.g. erroneous communication to PINPad, internal error, not used anymore

EMV_STATUS_TLV_BUILD_ERR 

CT & CTLS: Error in TLV data object = internal error

EMV_STATUS_FALLBACK 

CT & CTLS: Fallback to chip/msr (for CTLS) respectively magstripe (for CT) must be done

EMV_STATUS_ONL_PIN_REPEAT 

CT: wrong Online-PIN, repeat transaction (reduced) beginning with EMV_CT_StartTransaction() / EMV_CTLS_SetupTransaction()

EMV_STATUS_MAND_ELEM_MISSING 

CT: mandatory (TLV) element missing (EMV-configuration), not used anymore

EMV_STATUS_INVALID_TERM_CAP 

CT & CTLS: invalid terminal capabilities (EMV-configuration), not used anymore

EMV_STATUS_REFERRAL 

CT: a referral of the application decides if the TXN is approved or not

EMV_STATUS_2_CTLS_CARDS 

CTLS: 2 CTLS cards in the field detected. If this is reported after a call to ContinueOffline 2 cards have been detected in the field. The transaction is terminated in this case and must be restarted with a new call of SetupTransaction. This is mandatory for the VFI-Reader ADK and optional (but works as well) for teh Velocity/VERTX based ADK.

EMV_STATUS_TXN_CTLS_L1_ERR 

CTLS: level 1 problem, retap necessary

EMV_STATUS_TXN_CTLS_MOBILE 

CTLS: mobile device, retap necessary

EMV_STATUS_TXN_EMPTY_LIST 

CTLS: empty candidate list. The application shall display "please use other interface" and (depending on regional market requirements) additionally "or tap another card" CT & CTLS: Empty candidate List = no common application between card and terminal. For CT usually EMV_STATUS_FALLBACK is returned in any case, card error and empty list. If the caller needs to distinguish these cases, she has to enable this return code via EMVConf::setTransactionOptions() bit EMV_CT_SELOP_DETECT_EMPTY_LIST

EMV_STATUS_TXN_CTLS_EMV_USE_OTHER_CARD 

CTLS: insert, swipe or try another card

EMV_STATUS_CTLS_DOMESTIC_ONLY_NOT_READABLE 

CTLS: domestic not readable (no AID and EMV not configured)

EMV_STATUS_CONTINUE 

CT & CTLS: Transaction can be continued (e.g. CTLS Commit)

◆ EMVStatusInformation

enum EMVStatusInformation

EMV status information bits returned by EMVTxn::getEMVStatus()

Enumerator
EMV_SI_ONLINE_PIN_REQUIRED 

this means Online PIN CVM was performed during the transaction (CT: already done in a callback by the app, CTLS: to be performed by the app once the card is out of the field) --> Online PIN processing (host encryption) is required if the transaction is not declined or if there is no fallback.

EMV_SI_SIGNATURE_REQUIRED 

this means signature CVM was performed and the signature line must be printed on the receipt if the transaction is not declined or if there is no fallback.

EMV_SI_FORCED_ACCEPTANCE 

Forced acceptance transaction

EMV_SI_USER_DEFINED_CVM 

user defined CVM, this means that a custom CVM was performed and according to custom/domestic rules additional steps may apply

EMV_SI_ON_DEVICE_CVM 

An On-Device CVM was performed (Amex: "Mobile CVM", Visa: "Consumer device CVM"). Caution, obsolete: For VFI-Reader it indicates if CVM has been performed on the consumer device even if transaction flow CVM was no CVM (e.g. because below CVM-Limit). But for VERTEX this bit is set if CD-CVM is indicated in the kernel outcome with exception for Amex. Replaced by EMV_SI_CONSUMER_DEVICE and EMV_SI_OUTCOME_CD_CVM with a consistent behaviour.

EMV_SI_CUSTOMER_CARDWITHDRAWL 
EMV_SI_GICC_TIPPABLE 

A tip transaction may follow this payment

EMV_SI_PTC_EXCEEDED 

PIN try counter exceeded

EMV_SI_PIN_FAILURE 

Last entered offline PIN was wrong

EMV_SI_CONTACTLESS_CHIP 

A contactless chip transaction

EMV_SI_CONTACTLESS_MSR 

A contactless magstripe txn

EMV_SI_TORN_CREATED 

A torn transaction was created (PP3)
not used for contact

EMV_SI_TORN_TRY_RECOVER 

A torn transaction was tried to recover
not used for contact

EMV_SI_CONTACTLESS_WAITING 

The contactless transaction is still in the card waiting phase

EMV_SI_CONTACT_ONGOING 

The contact transaction is still ongoing

EMV_SI_CTLS_LONG_TAP 

Contactless "long tap", only appears if transaction goes online, card has to remain in field until EMV_CTLS_ContinueOnline() returned

EMV_SI_ARQC_RESTART_ANY 

Contactless kernel asks for second activation after online request in any case even in case of online problem (e.g. girocard OUT.ORD=ANY)

EMV_SI_ARQC_RESTART_UTGO 

Contactless kernel set OUT.ORD to EMV&OTGO and conditions for offline approval are valid. Retap required if unable to go online or script/auth data available.

EMV_SI_CONSUMER_DEVICE 

Contactless transaction performed by a consumer device (smart phone, tablet, watch) supporting CD-CVM (Consumer Device Cardholder Verification Method).

EMV_SI_CONTACTLESS_ONLY 

Contactless device, key fob or mini card without alternate interfaces. Note: This bit is derived from various card properties like "switch interface" or form factor indicators and is not reliable for all schemes. Don't use this information for control flow. It is intended as additional information or for statistics.

EMV_SI_OUTCOME_CD_CVM 

Contactless set if kernel Outcome Parameter CVM = Confirmation Code Verified (Consumer Device CVM successfully performed, see Book A)

EMV_SI_OUTCOME_RECEIPT 

Contactless set if kernel Outcome Parameter Receipt = Yes (provide a receipt, see Book A). Note: For instance only supported for MasterCard, girocard, JCB and RuPay.

EMV_SI_WRITE_DS_FAILED 

Contact Write data storage has failed

EMV_SI_ARQC_RESTART_FORBIDDEN 

Do not prompt for re-tap, no matter if there are issuer authentication data or scripts. This is a requirement for JCB online outcome neither 2 presentments nor present and hold and other kernels (e.g. Gemalto-PURE). It is also set for kernels that do not process issuer update at all (e.g. MasterCard, Visa, Amex, CUP, ...) and contactless mag. stripe transactions

EMV_SI_ARQC_RESTART_NO_IAUTHD 

Only prompt for re-tap in case issuer scripts are present, that is discard Issuer Authentication Data (IAuD, tag '91'). This flag is set for Discover and WISE transactions.

◆ EMVTransactionOptionBits

enum EMVTransactionOptionBits

EMV transaction option bits

Enumerator
EMV_CT_SELOP_CBCK_APPLI_SEL 

Callback function for customer application selection set by SDIClient::setEMVCallback (EMV_CB_AMOUNT_CONFIRMATION) will be generated, if there are several application possible.
Depends on EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS, EMVTxn::setNoCardholderConfirm.

EMV_CT_SELOP_RESERV_ALLOW_B_ON_A 

allow reservation type B even in case only type A is activated via configuration (see EMVSpecialTransactions )

EMV_CT_SELOP_CBCK_DOMESTIC_APPS 

Activate callback function for cross check if a domestic app remains in the candidate list or not (SDIClient::setEMVCallback (EMV_CB_DOMESTIC_APPS))
Depends on EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS

EMV_CT_SELOP_ADDALL 

Add all PSE applications to the candidate list (Cartes Bancaires - France)

EMV_CT_SELOP_ADDBLO 

Add blocked LOA applications to the candidate list (Interac - Canada)

EMV_CT_NO_LONGEST_AID_MATCH 

Do not perform the longest AID match (technical nonsense but needed for a few domestic certifcations)

EMV_CT_ALLOW_BLOCKED 

Allow blocked application to be processed (in Bank controlled terminals to enable script processing to unblock blocked cards)

EMV_CT_SELOP_REMOVEALL_BUT_EXCLUDED 

Remove all candidates from terminal list except those which are contained in excluded AID list

EMV_CT_TXNOP_PIN_BYPASS_NO_SUBSEQUENT 

If PIN bypass is supported it usually is for subsequent PIN entries, too. However some ICS (even if minor change) may announce no subsequent PIN Bypass, so you can configure here

EMV_CT_TXNOP_MULTIPLE_RANDOM_NUMBERS 

Create a new value for 9F37, each time a random number is requested by the ICC. Per default one random number per transaction is generated. It is recommended to use multiple random numbers for security reasons.

EMV_CT_TXNOP_DCC_CALLBACK 

DCC callback function set by SDIClient::setEMVCallback (EMV_CB_DCC) will be invoked.
Callback is only invoked if DCC is allowed (trann amount was not yet used in PDOL or amount confirmation) resp. limit conversion is needed (transaction and configuration currency difference).
Depends on EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS and EMV_CT_DCC_CHECK.

EMV_CT_TXNOP_DCC_CALLBACK_ALWAYS 

DCC callback funtion set by SDIClient::setEMVCallback (EMV_CB_DCC) will be called always.
Depends on EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS and EMV_CT_DCC_CHECK.

EMV_CT_TXNOP_NO_FALLBACK_AFTER_CVM 

Despite fallback after CVM allowed by appliction configuration stop transaction with card error. This is required in case of separate readers if mag. stripe has not been read prior to chip.

EMV_CT_TXNOP_AMOUNT_CONF 

The callback for the amount confirmation will be generated, e.g. to be deactivated if terminal is unattended.
Invoking this callback depends on EMV_CT_CONF_AMOUNT_PIN, EMV_CT_REFUND_CONFIRM_AMOUNT, EMV_CT_AMOUNT_CONFIRM_ON_SIGNATURE, EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS.

EMV_CT_TXNOP_ENFORCE_PIN 

Austrian (EPA) domestic feature: force PIN usage
In case no PIN entry was done during Cardholder Verification: EMV ADK will force online PIN entry.

EMV_CT_TXNOP_FALLBACK_GOODSERVICE 

German domestic feature: Execute cash transaction with transaction type "Goods & Services" (in case application's background system does not support cash)

EMV_CT_TXNOP_MERCHINFO_CALLBACK 

The callback for the intermediate merchant information will be generated (SDIClient::setEMVCallback EMV_CB_MERCHANT_INFO)
Depends on EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS

EMV_CT_TXNOP_RND_CALLBACK 

Use own random number generator instead of OS one (not recommneded but for debug purposes useful), only for velocity kernel, see EMV_CB_RANDOM

Deprecated:
not supported any more
EMV_CT_TXNOP_HOTLST_LOG_CALLBACK 

The callback for the transaction log / hotlist will be generated set by SDIClient::setEMVCallback (EMV_CB_CHECK_LOG_HOTLIST)
Depends on the AID parameters EMV_CT_TRANSACTION_LOG and EMV_CT_BLACKLIST, and on EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS

EMV_CT_TXNOP_LOCAL_CHCK_CALLBACK 

The callback for the domestic and local checks will be generated set by SDIClient::setEMVCallback (EMV_CB_DOMESTIC_APPS)
Depends on the AID parameter EMV_CT_DOMESTIC_CHECK and on EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS

EMV_CT_TXNOP_CARDHINFO_CALLBACK 

The callback for the intermediate cardholder information will be generated set by SDIClient::setEMVCallback (EMV_CB_CARDHOLDER_INFO)
Depends on EMV_CT_MS_RETURN_CALLBACKS

EMV_CT_TXNOP_EARLY_PIN_ENTRY 

Early PIN entry.
PIN entry is done (by application) in parallel to steps "Read application data" and "Offline data authentication".
Depends on EMV_CT_TXNOP_DELAYED_EARLY_PIN.
If set: Application starts PIN entry after GPO, in callback "merchant info - start read record" (SDIClient::setEMVCallback EMV_CB_MERCHANT_INFO with #EMVMER_READ_APP_DATA)
If not set: Application starts PIN entry at callback "local checks" (SDIClient::setEMVCallback with EMV_CB_LOCAL_CHECKS).

EMV_CT_TXNOP_DELAYED_EARLY_PIN 

Delayed early PIN entry.
PIN entry is done (by application) after callback "local checks" (SDIClient::setEMVCallback with EMV_CB_LOCAL_CHECKS).
Precondition: EMV_CT_TXNOP_EARLY_PIN_ENTRY is active.

EMV_CT_TXNOP_KERNEL_PARSE_UNKNOWN_TLV 

Let the kernel parse and store unknown TLV templates so that unknown tags can be retrieved by EMV_CT_fetchTxnTags. Precondition is that those tags are configured in the additional tag store (Additional_Tags_CRD)

EMV_CT_SELOP_NO_UTF8 

Omit UTF-8 converted application labels in application selection callback TAG_BF04_CBK_REDUCE_CAND

Note
This bit shares the bit position with EMV_CT_TRXOP_NO_UTF8
EMV_CT_TRXOP_NO_UTF8 

Omit UTF-8 converted application labels in amount confirmation and PIN input callback functions (TAG_BF02_CBK_AMOUNTCONF, TAG_BF08_CBK_PIN)

Note
This bit shares the bit position with EMV_CT_SELOP_NO_UTF8
EMV_CT_TXNOP_TIP_AMOUNT_ZERO 

Card holder confirmed zero amount within tip amount input dialog. In case of TIP setting DF22 position 4 = 3 the transaction shall not be made suitable for a tip follow-up.

EMV_CT_TRXOP_NO_CHECK_BB_PADDING 

Omit check for BB padding in card data authentication certificates - This check is obliged in some regions but not generally by EMVCo

EMV_CT_TRXOP_NO_CHECK_DDLEN 

Omit check if dynamic data length in card data authentication certificates is too big

EMV_CT_ONL_OPTS_LAST_PIN_TRY 

Host detected "last PIN try" for online PIN.

EMV_CT_TXNOP_PERFORM_ISS_ACQ_CVM 

Currently not used! The callback for AcquirerCVM processing

EMV_CT_TRXOP_WRITE_DS_OFFLINE_TXN 

Write data storage data for offline transactions. Relevant only by Continue Online. When this option is set, EMV_CTLS_ContinueOnline will only write the DS data and will not perform the kernel online processing.

EMV_CT_TXNOP_FORCE_TACIAC_DEFAULT 

After Host Connection: Force TAC IAC Default processing even the host was reached, e.g. service provider host is available and returns valid AC but the issuer host was not reached fro cryptogram verification

EMV_CT_SELOP_WEEK_PRIORITY_APPS 

Ignore priority applications that are not part of the terminal candidate list.

EMV_CT_CUST_APPLI_SELECTION_PERFORMED 

This is a possibility that allows the app to indicate that a customer application selection has been performed. If this is set, the callback / Reentrance for candidate selection will be even called if only one candidate is left. This is to inform the customer that the prior selected application was withdrawn from the candidate list after customer confirmation. In this special case a single candidate must not be selected automatically.

EMV_CT_SELOP_DETECT_EMPTY_LIST 

Without this bit in case of card error and in case of no common candidate EMV_STATUS_FALLBACK is returned for backwards compatibility. If enabled, the second case results in return code EMV_STATUS_TXN_EMPTY_LIST.

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_SUPPRESS_ERRMSGBEEP 

Suppress beep on error message display

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_REPEAT_L1 

TXN repeated because of L1 error (same txn is started a 2nd time)

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_NO_DOMESTIC_KERNEL 

skip local kernel processing for this transaction even if configured

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_NO_GLOBAL 

skip global EMV processing for this transaction even if configured

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_PP_TORNTXN_RESET 

reset the torn transaction store if a PayPass card is presented

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_AK_DELAYED_AUTH 

Amex delayed autorization (amex 3.1 and above), set this bit if after an Amex txn the host is not reachable (allows a retap with AAC or TC decision)

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_REMOVEALL_BUT_EXCLUDED 

B1b8: Remove all candidates from terminal list except those which are contained in excluded AID list

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_CANDLIST_CALLBACK 

common candidate list of terminal and card reported, see EMV_CB_MODIFY_CANDIDATES

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_APPSELECTED_CALLBACK 

callback after the final select, only available for velocity kernel, see EMV_CB_APP_SELECTED

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_NO_BUL12 

SU Bulletin 12 NOT supported (Velocitoy Entrypoint NOT EMVEP_CFG_BUL12)

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_NO_LONGEST_AID_MATCH 

Do not perform the longest AID match (technical nonsense but needed for a few domestic certifcations)

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_SPURIOUS_CARD_DETECT 

Try to avoid spurious card detections on ADK level (workaround for L1 issues, code provided by platform team)

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_NO_PAN_RETRIEVE_DEF 

PayPass: Do NOT Use default configuration for PAN Retrieval Transactions but configured values.
For all other schemes EMV ADK does anyhow use configured values for PAN retrieval transactions.
Not yet supported for VFI reader.

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_RND_CALLBACK 

Use own random number generator instead of OS one (not recommneded but for debug purposes useful), only supported for velocity kernel, see EMV_CB_RANDOM

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_OMIT_CHECKSUM_CHECK 

VFI-Reader: Dont calculate checksums of configuration files
Only effective on EMV_CTLS_SetupTransaction()

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_STOP_ON_CHKSUM_DIFF 

VFI-Reader: abort transaction when checksums of configuration files changed
Only effective on EMV_CTLS_SetupTransaction()

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_NO_AMOUNT_PRECHECK 

Disable the amount precheck --> even tap card is requested (Setup successful) if the txn amount is higher than the highest transaction limit of any AID / kernel. --> This results in terminate or fallabck later on

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_L1_ERROR_CALLBACK 

Enable notification callback for display "Error, try again" (EMV_TXT_RETAP_SAME_L1) in case of L1 error and "Use 1 card only" (EMV_TXT_2_CARDS_IN_FIELD) in case 2 cards are detected
Precondition: UI scheme "default" is set, use EMV_CTLS_UI_SCHEME_DEFAULT

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_SETUP_WAIT_FOR_ERROR 

VFI-Reader: EMV_CTLS_SetupTransaction() waits 10 ms for a negative answer from VFI-Reader so in case of VFI-Reader having problems, this is already detected in EMV_CTLS_SetupTransaction() rather than in EMV_CTLS_ContinueOffline().

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_WEEK_PRIORITY_APPS 

Ignore priority applications that are not part of the terminal candidate list

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_PRELOAD_TRANSACTION 

Preload feature: perform preliminary process and prepare database for payment without starting the transaction. Required for VAS processing using NFC ADK on VFI reader.

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_KEEP_MULTIPLE_KERNEL 

After Final Select keep all AID-kernel combinations for the selected AID

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_TIP_AMOUNT_ZERO 

Card holder confirmed zero amount within tip amount input dialog. In case of TIP setting DF22 position 4 = 3 the the transaction shall not be made suitable for a tip follow-up.

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_SILENT_ON_EMPTY_LIST 

In case of empty candidate list (return code EMV_STATUS_TXN_EMPTY_LIST) suppress error tone and LED processing (LEDs off after 750ms).

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_CVM_REQUIRED 

Force CVM for this transaction due to a special business use case. Basically implemented by internally setting the CVM required limits to zero.

EMV_CTLS_TXNOP_LONG_TAP_TIMER 

Set timer for Present And Hold timeout function according JCB Contactless IC Terminal Specification with value of Removal Timeout unless 0. In case of timeout contactless field is powered-off, "Card Read OK" display request is sent and light and sound indicators are triggered. For details please see Present And Hold Transaction ("Long Tap")

◆ MSROptions

enum MSROptions

MSR Options

Enumerator
MSR_UX_ENHANCEMENTS 

Relevant for UX, V/OS only: use improved noise filter and ignore card insertion, only read on card removal.

MSR_SAMSUNG_TRACK1 

Relevant for Samsung LoopPay only: continuous polling of Samsung LoopPay device to fetch track 1 data, if not set will deliver track 2 as soon as any data is read.

MSR_ONE_SWIPE 

In opposite to default behavior only read first swiped card after each call of MSR_Activate(). Subsequently swiped cards will not be read and will not overwrite the stored data. The stored data is deleted as usually upon call of MSR_GetData() or MSR_Deactivate(). To read the next card application has to call MSR_Deactivate() and MSR_Activate().

MSR_LEDS 

Light MSR LEDs while card swipe is possible.

MSR_ENABLE_LICENSE_DECODE 

Enable the decoding of California Drivers License and American Association of Motor Vehicle Administrators (AAMVA) Drivers License. By default, this option is disabled.

MSR_DETECT_ISO 

Detect ISO cards, this is the default and presumed if MSR_DETECT_JIS_II is not set.

MSR_DETECT_JIS_II 

Detect JIS-II cards. Currently only supported on V/OS2.

MSR_DETECT_ALL 

Detect both ISO and JIS-II cards. JIS-II cards currently only supported on V/OS2.

◆ PrtPropertyInt

enum PrtPropertyInt

Int type printer properties

Enumerator
PRT_PROP_STATE 

printer state (just using the subset of PrtError that reflects the state (read only)

PRT_PROP_HEAD_TEMP 

Head temperature value in degrees Celsius (read only)

Note
V/OS does not support reading the head temperature
PRT_PROP_HEAD_VOLTAGE 

Head voltage value in mV (read only)

PRT_PROP_PIXEL_WIDTH 

printer width in pixels, this may be 0 if the printer is temporarily not available. (read only)

printer contrast 0...255

Note
Setting the contrast will only show some effect if the underlying system supports it.
PRT_PROP_DEFAULT_FONT_SIZE 

Default font size

PRT_PROP_PRINT_MODE 

Preferred print mode: PRT_PREFER_GRAPHICS (default) or PRT_PREFER_TEXT, ignored if not supported by the printer

PRT_PROP_JS_QUOTA_SIZE 

If >0 filesystem quota in kilobytes for use by JavaScript, see also PRT_PROP_JS_QUOTA_ROOT

◆ PrtPropertyString

enum PrtPropertyString

String type printer properties

Enumerator
PRT_PROP_RESOURCE_PATH 

Resource path, default is resource/print

PRT_PROP_FILE_PREFIX 

prefix that is added in front of the URL in uiInvokeURL and to the template names, e.g. using "en/" would access the files in the subdirectory "en".

PRT_PROP_DEFAULT_FONT 

Default font name

PRT_PROP_CSS 

name of a CSS file

PRT_PROP_INIFILE 

name of the INI file, setting this property has the effect of reading and evaluating that file, i.e. the default font, font size and the CSS file name are updated

PRT_PROP_JS_ROOT 

Setting this path activates the JavaScript filesystem module. I/O is restricted to happen inside this path. Use "$APPDIR" to refer to this path from within JavaScript. Images and videos may also use "$APPDIR" to refer to files in this path.

PRT_PROP_DEVICE 

If not empty, printer device to be used on server side, e.g. /dev/ttyAMA0, not supported on all platforms, only devices that are accessibly by the printer server can be used

PRT_PROP_JS_QUOTA_ROOT 

If not empty base directory for quota JavaScript calculation, default is "", see also PRT_PROP_JS_QUOTA_SIZE

PRT_PROP_CP_APP_DIR 

CP app directory, if set only receipts from the app dir can be printed. It should point to the base app directory without platform, e.g. /home/sys14/www/<app-id> on V/OS

Key Encryption Key

SEC_KEY_TYPE_DUKPT 

DUKPT key

SEC_KEY_TYPE_CERT 

Certificate

SEC_KEY_TYPE_DIRECT_MK_PLAIN 

iPS_LoadMasterClearKey replacement. Loads the security script’s master key. The values are sent in the clear, but must all be loaded in the same session.
Before loading the first key after a power cycle, all previously loaded keys (including the system keys) are erased.

This function should be used exclusively in a secure environment.

SEC_KEY_TYPE_DIRECT_MK_ENC 

iPS_LoadMasterEncKey replacement. Loads the security script’s master key without deleting the keys already loaded. The key value must be encrypted with VSS_KLK

SEC_KEY_TYPE_DIRECT_SYSK_PLAIN 

iPS_LoadSysClearKey replacement. Loads the VSS_KLK (system key) in the clear.
Before writing the new value of the key, all other keys in the terminal are erased.

This function should be used exclusively in a secure environment.

SEC_KEY_TYPE_DIRECT_SYSK_ENC 

iPS_LoadSysEncKey replacement. Loads the system key. The new values must be encrypted under the current value of VSS_KLK.

SEC_KEY_TYPE_DELETE_ALL_KEYS 

iPS_DeleteKey replacement.

SEC_KEY_TYPE_DELETE_SYS_KEY 

iPS_DeleteKey replacement.

SEC_KEY_TYPE_DIRECT_AUTHEX_ENC 

rsaAuthexVssKeyInstall replacement. Loads the VSS key. The new values must be encrypted under AuthEx.

SEC_KEY_TYPE_DIRECT_AUTHEX_SYSK 

rsaAuthexVssKeyInstall replacement. Loads the VSS_KLK. The new values must be encrypted under AuthEx.

◆ TECStartOptions

enum TECStartOptions

SDI TEC start options (bit mask)

Enumerator
TEC_NFC_ENABLE 

CTLS, only allowed if CTS_VAS_ENABLE is NOT set: ADK-NFC is used for detection of contactless cards, options[12..15] determine which NFC technology is enabled.

TEC_VAS_ENABLE 

CTLS, only allowed if CTS_NFC_ENABLE is NOT set: ADK-NFC is used for Wallet processing.

TEC_EMV_AFTER_NFC_ISO 

Relevant only if CTS_NFC_ENABLE is set. Perform an EMV transaction if NFC has detected one of the following cards: I_ISO14443A, I_ISO14443B

TEC_VAS_HANDLE_LED_BUZZ 

Relevant only if CTS_VAS_ENABLE is set: Handle LEDs and buzzer if VAS processing failed or VAS only (no subsequent EMV transaction).

TEC_EMV_CTLS_TIMEOUT_AFTER_VAS 

Relevant only if CTS_VAS_ENABLE is set: This option enables the use of a permissible time window to perform a contactless payment after either VAS_DO_PAY or VAS_DO_PAY_DECRYPT_REQ has been detected. The dimension of this time window is configured with the input parameter options[10..11] of the function cts_StartSelection().

TEC_VAS_DONT_DECRYPT 

Relevant only if CTS_VAS_ENABLE is set: TEC will NOT decrypt the resulting VAS data.

TEC_MSR_AFTER_CTLS_FAIL 

Relevant only if options[6..7] is set: Wait for MSR read after CTLS transaction only if that failed.

TEC_NFC_DUTY_CYCLE_OFF 

Relevant only if CTS_NFC_ENABLE is set. Ux700 overheat protection (duty cycle) is turned on by default. Can be switched off by this bit.

TEC_PURE_CARD_DETECTION 

Relevant for CTLS only: only detect card, do not perform transaction

TEC_NO_POWERON 

Relevant for CT only (must not be set in conjunction with TEC_POWERON_AFTER_CTLS_MSR_DEACTIVATION): do not power on inserted card.

TEC_POWERON_AFTER_CTLS_MSR_DEACTIVATION 

Relevant for CT only (must not be set in conjunction with TEC_NO_POWERON): deactivate CTLS and MRS once chip-card is detected and then power on the chip-card.
